Message-ID: <fc2d5007-111a-583a-d5d0-b48c07863391@imbi.uni-freiburg.de>

Daniel,

The maximum value you can get for arcsine transformed proportions is 
1.571 (for a proportion of 100%) which you can see using the following R 
command: asin(sqrt(1))

Accordingly, the intercept 3.06 in your meta-regression is way of the 
mark due to extrapolating the effect of the continuous variable year. 
The intercept represents the effect at year 0 A.D.

I would suggest that you center the variable year around some value.

Best wishes, Guido

