Dear Rebecca,


The code you used "doesn't know" whether a study is three-arm. You still 
calculate SMD for each two arms, ignoring the third. Though you have 
already a netmeta-compatible structure, the structure of your data makes 
it more difficult in this case because of the problems with the SMDs. 
Better to start with a different structure and to use pairwise().


Function pairwise() expects

- either a format with one row per study and three (say) blocks of 
columns (studlab, TR1, TR2, TR3, n1, n2, n3, mean1, mean2, mean3, sd1, 
sd2, sd3, ...);? for an example see help(dietaryfat),

- or an arm-based format with one row per study arm like this (for an 
example of the second kind, see help(Woods2010)):


studlab TR??? n? mean??? sd

107???? MBI? 68 46.90 18.20

107???? PE?? 68 50.60 18.50

107???? PsEd 66 55.20 15.30

...???? ...? .. ..... .....


Hope this helps.


Best,

Gerta


